<item>
            <title>[FELIX-850] Wrong symbolic name computed when groupId is a single segment string.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-850</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;According to the documentation, a bundles symbolic name should follow respect the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;if artifactId starts with last section of groupId that portion is removed. eg. org.apache.maven:maven-core -&amp;gt; org.apache.maven.core&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;however, when the groupId a single segment, this rule is ignored.  Thus a groupId of smx3 and artifactId of smx3.testing gets a symbolic name of smx3.smx3.testing.  When it should just be smx3.testing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
